* fix the command run on windows in exec tasks

In EXEC* tasks on windows, if slashes are used for the executable, the resulted
command executed is:

EXECUTABLE EXECUTABLE ARGUMENTS

with the first EXECUTABLE having antislashes and the second one slashes.

This patch returns the command to its normal form :

EXECUTABLE ARGUMENTS

Redo the database objects organization.

- Split all database objects into 2 classes :
- a POJO class (singular name) with no methods or constructors that only represent its respective database object
- a utility class with only static methods to manipulate the corresponding database table and database object
- (when applicable) a POJO class that represents the available filters for the corresponding database table
- Move all these classes into sub-packages that separate them by their respective database tables
- Move Calendar utility methods from `Transfer` to `HandlerUtils` for better accessibility
- Changed the `replace` and `delete` methods to take the table primary key instead of the database entry to avoid unhandled
errors when trying to modify a non-existant entry

Note : all POJO database classes have all their fields public to allow them to be read/written by an ObjectMapper and converted to/from JSON.
